# Why I Chose This Architecture

I intentionally avoided deploying everything inside a single virtual machine.

Instead, I wanted to simulate how enterprise organizations build cloud platforms.

Some of the design decisions I made include:

- Stateless microservices running on AKS
- Service-to-service communication through Istio
- Gateway API using kgateway
- Azure Front Door for global traffic management
- Application Gateway for Layer-7 routing and Web Application Firewall
- Azure Service Bus for asynchronous image processing
- Azure Blob Storage for storing generated images
- Azure Key Vault for secret management
- GitOps deployment with Argo CD

This architecture provides scalability, security, and operational flexibility.

